<br>
Note: Without IP, I can not even get out of the blast radius of a MoC PBAoE caster fast enough on sprint to live.  Getting hit by PBAoE is not so bad, just like when I get the initiative and whack casters with my axe is not so bad.  What IS bad is the fact that I hit squishy cloth casters for 300 damage every 5 seconds, but they hit me for 500 damage every 1 second.<br>
<br>
Note 2: Some uber players swear by Avoid Pain.  They site the lag inherent in IP.  I don't have the RPs to afford AP yet, but I can atest to the fact that IP fails to go off in many fights exactly when you need it, in a way that Purge never fails.  Sometimes the button greys out a half second after I hit it, and I am not stunned/mezzed, I am being hit/dotted, and I die before it becomes pushable again.<br>
<br>
Purge: I try to save it for bad fights when I need to IP (in case I am stunned by enemy tanks, enemy stun tends to last long enough to kill me even with my capped resists).  The goal for Purge always seems to be to Purge in time to sprint and live while the rest of the group kills.  The fun fights allow a Purge then a good target selection or /assist.<br>
<br>
That's it.  I like MoP, but it doesn't do much and every tank gets it.<br>
<br>
Lifter:  The saving grace, an RA most do not take to level 2.  I always have a ram, and it makes the game more fun for me because it makes me useful on the spot.  Not exactly unique, then again not much to choose from...<br>
<br>
** Wouldn't it be cool if ALL RAs were available to everyone?  Then we could truly place a value on RAs.  Why do I have to be gimp to start, but also pay more for IP than tanks?  Why can't I have access to Determination?  How many would take the Skald unique RA?<br>
<br>
ZERO<br>
<br>
How many would take SoS?  Everyone with a brain.<br>
<br>
There is this one group of Albs we fight a lot, one of the best Alb groups.  Know what they have?  SoS bots.  Not active SoS Minstrels, Bots.  Not one but at least 2 (they leave one at the pk).  When they come out, if they get the jump on us, they fight and kill us with BoF.  If we get the jump on them, they SoS and run each and every time.  They come back minutes later with a new SoS.  If we jump em, SoS and run.  Then they wait for SoS to recycle.  Guess who has the higher IRS score?  SoS is faster than skald speed too.<br>
<br>
-Leitari, MLF <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maximumstorage>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/03 9:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=662.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skalds, What RAs do you use . . .</span><hr size=1> str1, dex2(only because I have to get it for mastery of pain), conII, toughII, AvoidMagic1, long wind1, mastery of parry2, master of pain 2, those are all the passives I can afford with buying purge and IP. I could have gotten conIII and avoid pain2 and IP but then I would have no points left over for any passives. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=woggha>Woggha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/03 3:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=662.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SOS Speed</span><hr size=1> Just to make it clear, SOS is NOT faster than Skald speed. Sos is 200%, Skald speed is 204% <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=courtjester@teamskald>CourtJester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/03 5:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fte