<br>
You only gain when you are RR5+ fighting some newb RR2 enemy without IP.<br>
<br>
I do think we have a role not many have described yet though.  Can we use our 4 instas to interrupt enemy casters better than anyone else?  If we focus on asking for more range for those shouts we might have an edge to explore!  Currently everything but the snare has a very annoying short range.  If I could take an enemy healer out of action for the entire fight via interrupts I would value myself more highly.<br>
<br>
Issue there is that lately I am getting mezzed multiple times per fight.  The 1 minute immunity is easy to get around for the Hibs and Albs who seem to have more mez types than Mid (could be the shortage of SM on my server).  Mezzes on different resists ignore the immunity timer.  And I think the enemy is getting very good at cycling those mez types to avoiud the immunity timer altogether (just a hunch no tests so far, would be easy to test in a duel, duel healer, get mezzed, end duel, duel SM, get mezzed, end duel, return to healer all within a minute and see if his mez sticks). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gotterdaoc>GotterDAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/22/03 8:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=662.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://unforsakensouls.us/mask_square.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skalds, What RAs do you use . . .</span><hr size=1> You make a good point, especially considering that the next patch should see the end of interrupt shouts for Savages, Paladins, and anybody else who has a pulling shout that also interrupted as a side effect. <p>Gotter Dammerung - 50 skald<br />
